text: The Division of Cook is an Australian Electoral Division in New South Wales. It was set up in 1969 and is named for James Cook, who mapped the east coast of Australia in 1770. It is located in the southern suburbs of Sydney, including Caringbah, Cronulla, Miranda and Sylvania. ==Members== Member Party Term Don Dobie Liberal 1969–1972 Ray Thorburn Labor 1972–1975 Don Dobie Liberal 1975–1996 Stephen Mutch Liberal 1996–1998 Bruce Baird Liberal 1998–2007 (retired) Scott Morrison Liberal 2007–present In 2007 there were claims that the Liberal candidate Michael Towke had broken party rules and not told the truth about himself. These claims were later found to be not true.Sheehan, Paul. Nasty saga you nearly missed. The Sydney Morning Herald, 2009-10-26. Towke lost his Liberal party position and was replaced with Scott Morrison, former director of the New South Wales Liberal Party.http://psephos.adam-carr.net/countries/a/australia/2007seats/cook.shtml In 2013 Morrison became the Minister for Immigration and Border Protection. ==Election results== ==References== ==Other websites== * Division of Cook - Australian Electoral Commission * Scott Morrison's website Category:Electoral divisions of New South Wales Category:1969 establishments in Australia
